urls.title: Hack-a-TONx w/ DoraHacks | Hackathon | DoraHacks
urls.description: # Updates Hack-a-TONx Onboarding week is coming! Starting from Jan 30th, there will be a series 0-1 live workshops and Q&A sessions to help you join the ecosystem building (and get funded). You’re invited to ask questions and win coupons during the live sessions. [Important] Please put your questions at https://t.me/hackatonx/3078 (NOT via Binance Live comments!). You’ll be able to win AWS coupons! # Introduction [The Open Network (TON)](https://ton.org/) is a fully decentralized layer-1 Proof-of-Stake blockchain designed by **Telegram** and continued by the **open-source community** to usher in the next era of Web3 conversion and onboard **billions of users**. TON supports dynamic sharding, Turing-complete smart contracts, and upgradable formal blockchain specifications. It boasts ultra-fast transactions, low fees, and mobile-friendly dApps. TON aims to offer Web3 solutions via decentralized sites, proxy, and storage solutions on the blockchain rail. **New protocol. New opportunities.

urls.title: TON Society
urls.description: Looking for TON Content Leaders Dear TON Society residents, We invite you to co-promote TON’s first global hackathon by writing a blog post. Hack-a-TONx with Dorahacks will be held on Jan. 30 through March 31, 2023. We’re looking for people who will attract developers to the event with their insight and writing skills. Topic Any topic is fine if it can achieve the above goal. For example: ▪️Your prior TON hackathon or Smart Challenge experience ▪️What I wish I had known when first building on TON. Please don’t forget to include the hackathon information and encourage participation at the end of your post. Publishing Please publish your article on a popular developer blog, Medium, or LinkedIn. Email the article link to press@ton.org with the title Period We will gather and select 10 posts by Jan. 20, 2023, on a first-come-first-serve basis. Rewards Each qualified contributor will receive $300 in Toncoin.
